  "text": "Besides the game-theoretic capacity investment analyses, there is a stream of literature examining lumpy capacity investments using real options framework (e.g., Li and Wang (2010), [CITATION_1] , and Hahn and Kuhn (2012)). Even though time-to-build constraint is omitted in most of the game-theoretic models, it has been employed in growth literature emphasizing optimal corporate investment decisions. The corporate investment literature mainly incorporates real options view of investment and the standard net present value rule. To explain business cycles, some optimal growth models have incorporated time-to-build. [CITATION_2] ",
